I'm not biased because it was my wedding reception and I was half  responsible for picking it out (well, 40%, no, more like 23%), but this was seriously the best wedding cake I've ever had.  The cake itself was BEYOND 5 STARS - it was a multi teired beauty on a white wrought iron triple platform, simply smothered in fresh strawberries, blueberries, and rasberries.  So YUM.  The cake and frosting were an excellent consistency and perfectly not-too-sweet.  The only thing holding back the last star was an unfortunate situation during the select-your-cake appointment, where the previous appt ran long, and even though it was the customer's fault, not the cake-lady's, cake-lady didn't really do anything to try to speed them up, and her pained glances in our direction did not make us feel any better about sitting there listening to 3 humungous women ask to try each and every sample in the entire building.    Fleur De Lis seems very mom-and-pop-ish, but this I did not confirm.  They are affiliated with the Embassy (Fountain) Suites at Greenway as the one of the bakers from which you may choose your cake that is included with the wedding package, so we weren't sure what we'd be getting. But the cake was a big hit; I don't remember a single person not loving it, and we had to scramble to get the top put away for saving before everybody gobbled it all up.  I'll try to remember to add a pic because it was truly spectacular.

